## AgentMessageContent

v0.11 only supports `text` (file/image upload TBD in v0.12). v0.13 adds multi-session fields:

| Field | Type | Purpose |
|-------|------|---------|
| `text` | `string` | Plain text message — the only content type supported in v0.11 |
| `chat_session_id` | `string` | **[v0.13]** If non-empty, target agent stores this message under `pm:<from>:<chat_session_id>` — separate session with fresh LLM context. |
| `new_session` | `bool` | **[v0.13]** If `true` and `chat_session_id` is empty, server auto-generates a UUID. Convenient for "always new session" use cases like CI error alerts. |

### Multi-session behavior

| `chat_session_id` | `new_session` | Result |
|-------------------|---------------|--------|
| `""` (empty) | `false` | **Legacy**: target stores message under shared `pm:<from>` session (single conversation, all messages mixed). |
| `"cs_abc123..."` | (any) | **Explicit new session**: target stores under `pm:<from>:cs_abc123...`. |
| `""` (empty) | `true` | **Auto new session**: server generates `cs_<uuid>`, target stores under `pm:<from>:cs_<uuid>`. |

**When to use multi-session**:
- CI error alerts — each error gets fresh LLM context, no pollution from previous errors
- Per-task invocations — each task is independent, target agent doesn't get confused
- Per-user invocations — track which invocation produced which output

**When NOT to use**:
- Continuation tasks where you want the target to remember prior context
- Single-shot "fire and forget" where session doesn't matter

