## Server-side endpoint

`POST /api/v1/agent/invoke-stream` (no auth middleware — signature-based auth)

Request body:
```json
{
  "target_public_key": "...",  // 64-char hex Ed25519 public key
  "challenge": "...",          // hex challenge from /auth/challenge
  "signature": "...",          // Ed25519 signature of the challenge
  "content": "...",            // message text
  "content_type": "text",      // only "text" supported in v0.12
  "caller": "samai_ci",        // [v0.12] required — who is dispatching
  "timeout_seconds": 600,      // default 600 (10 min), max 3600
  "chat_session_id": "",       // [v0.13] optional — explicit session id
  "new_session": false         // [v0.13] optional — if true and no chat_session_id, server generates UUID
}
```

Response: `text/event-stream` (SSE) with events: `start` (includes `caller` + `chat_session_id` if set), `warning`, `chunk`, `end`, `cancel`, `error`.

The target agent receives the message as: `[invoke by <caller>] <original content>` — so it knows who invoked it.

